On the subjective nature of consciousness: "The subjective character of experience is the essential feature that distinguishes it from all other kinds of processes."
On the problem of consciousness: "The subjective character of experience seems to resist explanation in terms of anything purely objective."
On the moral status of animals: "If an animal has a subjective point of view, then it is wrong to inflict unnecessary suffering on it."
On the nature of morality: "Morality is not merely a matter of personal preference or social convention; it is grounded in objective reasons."
On the limitations of reason: "Reason alone cannot provide us with a complete guide to life; we also need intuition and emotion."
